Peru Stocks: Alturas, Buenaventura, Candente, Relapasa, Volcan

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-05T21:33:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/peru-stocks-alturas-candente-casa-grande-relapasa-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.2 percent to 20,638.49. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 1.1 percent to 2,711.20.  Peruvian mining and precious metal stocks dropped as
commodity prices declined. The Lima General Index rose the most
yesterday since Nov. 4, 2008, after a presidential poll before
next month’s election showed Congresswoman Keiko Fujimori
gaining on Ollanta Humala, leader of Peru’s Nationalist Party.  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, tumbled 5.6 percent to 17 cents as copper
fell to the lowest price in five months on the Comex in New
York.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, fell 5 percent to $1.52. Minas Buenaventura S.A. (BVN
PE), Peru’s biggest precious metals producer, fell 4 percent to
$39.60.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol TPF SA, dropped 1.6 percent to 1.85 soles as crude oil
retreated 8.6 percent in New York to $99.80 a barrel. Volcan Cia
Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver producer,
slipped 1.3 percent to 3.15 soles as silver for July delivery
fell 8 percent to $36.24 an ounce on the Comex in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
